### Description

So, in recent versions, we are able to provide titles for routes via a string or a resolver function. This issue was discovered when trying to use resolved data as a resolver for the page title.

In general, dynamic titles often rely on some HTTP calls to produce meaningful titles, and the issue of using already resolved data comes up if we do not want to: 

1. repeat the same HTTP call twice
2. move the dynamic title setup logic into a component

In this example, we have a resolver that resolves a product item, and then a dynamic title resolver that wants to reuse that resolved data. Which, of course, makes sense, as I already pulled the product data and just want to pluck the title of the product and use it as a title:

```typescript
export const productResolver: ResolveFn<Product> = ({ paramMap }) => {
  console.log('resolving product');
  const productService = inject(ProductService);
  const id = paramMap.get('id') ?? 0;
  return productService.getProductById(+id);
};

export const routes: Routes = [
  {
    path: 'product/:id',
    component: ProductComponent,
    title: () => {
      const route = inject(ActivatedRoute);
      return route.data.pipe(
        // this was an attempt to "wait" for the data
        // but it did not work, Observable never emits anything
        // skipWhile((data) => {
        //   return !data['product'];
        // }),
        map((data) => {
          console.log(data?.['product']?.title ?? 'Default');
          return data?.['product']?.title ?? 'Default';
        })
      );
    },
    resolve: { product: productResolver },
  },
];
```

When I access the resolved data via parameters (`title: ({data}) => {}`), I get an empty object. But, and this is important, the `productResolver` works just fine and I am able to read the product data in the component via input binding.

