### Anything else?

I am not entirely sure if this is a bug, could be intended behavior (all resolvers including the title resolver run in parallel, resulting in race conditions when trying to resolve the title). However, I would argue that running the title resolver *after* all other resolvers have finished would make more sense here. Also, if this is, in fact, the case, it is strange that even using `skipWhile` to wait does not seem to resolve the issue, it is as if the `data` Observable never emits for the title resolver, which makes me think this might even be a dependency injection issue (the title resolver gets a "wrong" `ActivatedRoute` instance)

